{"questionId":"9066799","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A student synthesized aspirin, acetylsalicylic acid, in a school laboratory.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c9c245870e2accc0b383195694d374f1ac1b8de0.png\" width=\"209\" height=\"272\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">0.300 g of crude aspirin was dissolved in ethanol and titrated with sodium hydroxide solution, NaOH (aq).</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NaOH (aq) + C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O4 (in ethanol) → NaC<sub>9</sub>H<sub>7</sub>O<sub>4</sub> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l)</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the percentage purity of the synthesized aspirin.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.293{\\text{ g}}}}{{{\\text{0}}{\\text{.300 g}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.293</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>0</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>.300 g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> × 100 % »= 97.7 «%»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066799","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.22b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the percentage purity of the synthesized aspirin.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.2 Aspirin and penicillin","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}